OL,3,CProlific fare dodger spared jail term
OL,4,Cover 112 unpaid train tickets
OL,6,FThe judge told Brohiri: "My view is,
OL,7,Fas is set out in the pre-sentence
OL,8,Freport (PSR), that you feel that you
OL,9,Fare invincible by committing these
OL,10,Foffences and that you see it as some
OL,11,Fsort of self-entitlement that you can
OL,12,Fget away with it."
OL,14,FShe also called his offending "brazen
OL,15,Fand persistent".
OL,17,FBut she added that the PSR showed he
OL,18,Fhas some insight into his crimes and
OL,19,Fthat probation could help him.
