OL,3,CProlific fare dodger spared jail term
OL,4,Cover 112 unpaid train tickets
OL,6,FThe judge sentenced him to three
OL,7,Fmonths in jail, suspended for a year.
OL,9,FBrohiri was also ordered to pay back
OL,10,F#3,629.60 in unpaid rail fares but he
OL,11,Fwas not ordered to pay prosecution
OL,12,Fcosts which the court heard amounted
OL,13,Fto #15,120.
OL,15,FHe was further ordered to complete 150
OL,16,Fhours of unpaid work, 12 months'
OL,17,Fprohibited activity requirement `
OL,18,Fwhich means he must not travel on any
OL,19,FGTR trains ` and to complete
OL,20,Frehabilitation activity requirement.
