OL,6,FShe said the pre-sentence report found
OL,7,FBrohiri has been facing personal
OL,8,Ftroubles but "understood the severity
OL,9,Fof the charges".
OL,11,F"He reiterated to me this morning that
OL,12,Fif he is given the opportunity to work
OL,13,Fwith probation they can assist him in
OL,14,Fsecuring accommodation and
OL,15,Femployment," Ms Curzon continued.
OL,17,F"It is really these two factors which
OL,18,Fwill put an end to Mr Brohiri's
OL,19,Foffending."
