OL,4,Cover 112 unpaid train tickets
OL,6,FShe told the court that he went to
OL,7,Funiversity but had to drop out and has
OL,8,Fworked as a waiter and in bars.
OL,10,FAsked what he has been doing in his
OL,11,Fthree years of being homeless in
OL,12,FLondon, Ms Curzon said Brohiri has
OL,13,Ftried to get support from charities
OL,14,F"but none of it has been consistent
OL,15,Fenough".
OL,17,FThe defendant will appear at the same
OL,18,Fcourt on March 29 for a means inquiry
OL,19,Fto assess whether he can pay further
OL,20,Fcosts.
